   \begin{align}
   (AB)_{ij} &= \sum_{k=1}^n A_{ik}B_{kj} \\
   (AB)^T_{ji} &= \sum_{k=1}^n A^T_{ki}B^T_{jk} \\
   \end{align}

   The transposed product \((AB)^T\) is an \(p \times m\) matrix.

2. **Transposing a Matrix**

   The transpose of a matrix \(A\) is denoted by \(A^T\). It is obtained by flipping the matrix along its main diagonal.

